    public interface IProcessor
extends ICLIOptionDefinitionProvider

    This interface defines processors that can perform arbitrary tasks when the process(Phase, Context) method is invoked.

    The process(Phase, Context) method can be invoked multiple times, once for each processing phase. Available phases are pre-processing phase, processing phase, and post-processing phase, as defined by the IProcessor.Phase enumeration.

    Usually classes should not implement this interface directly, but instead extend from the AbstractProcessor class.

    Author:
    Ruud Senden
